HEADWORD: Flyaway grass
<hw>Flyaway grass</hw>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The hair grass
(<spn>Agrostis scabra</spn>). So called from its light panicle, which is
blown to great distances by the wind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

